Cautionary note on the use of data in millions of
dollars -- The tables provided include estimates in
millions of dollars for NIPA series that appear regularly in the national income
and product account (NIPA) tables published in the Survey of Current Business.
The Bureau of Economic Analysis (BEA) generally does not include estimates at
this level of precision in the published tables because the associated sampling
and nonsampling errors are larger than this implied level of precision. Compared
with the published aggregates, the million-dollar estimates
are generally not any more accurate.

column3: Insurance payments to persons by business
Donations by corporate business to nonprofit institutions serving households
Defined benefit and defined contribution pension plans (net)
Net change in benefit entitlements for defined benefit plans \1\
Net change in assets from current transactions for defined contribution plans
Less: Total contributions and contribution supplements \2\
Payments to the rest of the world (net) \5\

column2: NA
1. Equals total household contributions and contribution supplements less benefit
payments and withdrawals; that is, net business current transfer payments for
defined benefit pension plans always equal zero.
2. Equals actual employer contributions plus imputed employer contributions plus
actual household contributions less pension service charges
plus household pension contribution supplements; see table 7.20.  All contributions
to defined benefit and defined contribution plans are considered to be from households.
3. Consists largely of losses by business due to fraud and unrecovered thefts,
corporate cash prizes, and payments from personal injury trust funds.
4. For detail, see table 3.7.
5. Consists of net insurance settlements paid to the rest of the world less net
insurance settlements received from the rest of the world.
